ss=title> /sigh</span><hr size=1> Ok, so Im pretty touchy on the subject and I dont like to get very vocal about it for a few reasons... but today, over a year later, something happened this morning that pretty much made me want to break down all over again.<br>
<br>
Driving along the expressway through downtown Grand Rapids we approach the city and the few tall buildings that we have... my 4 year old is sitting in the front seat beside me (yes, 4, front seat, so shoot me) and he starts to panic and cry...<br>
<br>
I cant exactly dodge traffic, pull over, and find out whats wrong without slamming into someone or something so I try to figure out what is going on (thinking maybe a bumble bee *shrug*)...<br>
<br>
Ends up he saw the smoke from the top of a large building (white smoke coming out of the top from the heat) and he thinks that an airplane crashed into the building and that everyone in it was going to die... it was a big building so the BIG cloud of white smoke was very easy to see.<br>
<br>
I explained to him that it was just the chimney and the smoke was just from the buildings heating system, and had to drive him around and point to other buildings that had the same thing.<br>
<br>
He calmed down and sat quietly for a while, and unable to think of what I could say/do to ease his mind I realized that Im completely clueless, as a mother, on how to deal with this situation.<br>
<br>
I know that for me the events of 9/11 stuck me into a deeper state of depression than I had already been dealing with... and I still havent recovered from all the events of that time period (RL issues as well like deaths in the family/divorce/etc...) but now not only am I effected by it I have a child (small, fragile, innocent, beautiful child mind you) who's living in fear that some bad people are going to crash a plane into his home or buildings around him and hurt people...<br>
<br>
I cant tell him it wont happen again...<br>
I cant tell him he's completely safe...<br>
I cant tell him the bad guys got caught...<br>
I cant tell him that I fear for his life each and every day...<br>
I cant tell him that there's hope...<br>
I cant tell him that mommy will come home from work every day...<br>
I cant tell him that we wont die tomorrow...<br>
I cant tell him that I can protect him from evil...<br>
<br>
so what can I tell him?<br>
<br>
he's almost 5 and he's seen so much... death, terrorism, divorce...<br>
<br>
I, as an adult, have a hard time dealing with this @#%$... but it kills me so much to see my little boy have to even worry about it... he should be worrying about where he left his red crayon... not worrying about whether or not someone is going to die today.<br>
<br>
Anyway... I guess I just wanted to vent.  I know there are no answers to those questions, I just needed to get it out. <p>Syldra Megiste` <br>
