<br>
A lot of people are living in fear over 9/11 and now a sniper in Washington, D.C. You certainly aren't alone in having to deal with a loved one (especially a child) who is fearful of the future, or at least of what the next moment will bring.<br>
<br>
It is at times like these that I think most invoke faith in something, such as a religious faith or maybe in an activity like prayer or meditation, to help cope.<br>
<br>
Things as simple as praying with a child instill hope in them and make them feel that things can get better.<br>
<br>
Another alternative is having your child talk with a children's counselor or a psychologist just to be sure he is doing ok.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I hope you don't mind me sharing some suggestions. <br>
<br>
